cs.HC, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.SD, cs.CL

Reasoning: 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on developing a wearable navigation device for blind people, which involves designing a user-friendly interface and considering the users' needs and preferences.
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also a likely category as the paper proposes a navigation system that involves locating, way-finding, route following, and obstacle avoiding modules, which are common components in robotics navigation systems.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a possible category as the proposed navigation device uses optical see-through glasses, which may involve computer vision techniques for image processing and object recognition.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper may involve software development for the navigation system and its components.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper may involve natural language processing techniques for providing audio instructions to the users.
